  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Component A: To strengthen understanding of and capacity for conflict sensitivity through a Conflict Sensitivity Hub
Component B: To enhance the effectiveness and advocacy capacity of peacebuilding actors in Eastern DRC through stronger coordination and representation

Output Area 1: Build a cadre of local conflict experts 
Output Area 2a: Conduct a review of best practices to support the design of the CS Hub 
Output Areas 2b: Conduct a needs assessment for FCDO partners on conflict sensitivity 
Output Area 3. Provide CS technical assistance services to FCDO and its partners in DRC 

Output Area 4: Secondment of Peacebuilding Coordinator into NGO Forum</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The need for a more systematic and sound application of Conflict Sensitivity best practices in aid interventions in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) has been recognised since many years and has become even more apparent with the recent developments due the COVID-19 pandemic that is exacerbating longstanding conflict dynamics and creating new ones.
Based on Alert&#x2019;s experience in developing and applying conflict sensitivity best practices to strategies and interventions in conflict affected contexts, we propose a 12-month project that will help shape the conversation and support learning for donors and implementing organisations on approaches to CS in DRC. Findings and lessons learned from this project can help inform the design of FCDO new programme for DRC as well as provide conflict sensitivity support to FCDO ongoing and future programmes, as discussed with FCDO Peace and Security Advisor in DRC.  

Peacebuilding organizations operating in DRC and some of their donors and stakeholders have recognized the need for peacebuilding efforts to be better coordinated and represented to increase their effectiveness both on the ground as well as on the strategic and advocacy level, in a working environment where coordination mechanisms are mainly focused on humanitarian and development needs and interventions. PB organizations and the NGO Forum have discussed about the opportunity to have a Peacebuilding coordinator representing them within the forum. The role of the Coordinator would be to coordinate PB organizations with regards to information sharing, conflict and context analysis, key advocacy messages and strategy.</narrative>
  </description>
